SIMPLE: ethylamine
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Ethylamine
<hw>Eth`yl*am"ine</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Ethyl</ets> + <ets>amine</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld>
<def>A colorless, mobile, inflammable liquid, <chform>C2H5.NH2</chform>,
very volatile and with an ammoniacal odor. It is a strong base, and is a
derivative of ammonia. Called also <altname>ethyl carbamine</altname>,
and <altname>amido ethane</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Ethylate</ent>⟦br⟧
